<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_Dynasty_Values" s="498866">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0xF316893<!--String: "Dynasty Values"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Values1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2437764d6043eb49</T>
      <T n="text">0xA6238E44<!--String: "The Dynasty Values are the heart of the Dynasty, as they define what kind of <b><font color='#199C2C'>Activities and Careers</font></b> are <b><font color='#199C2C'>Encouraged</font></b> and which ones are <b><font color='#199C2C'>Discouraged</font></b>. These are shown in a Tooltip when hovering over a Value. \n\nValues come in two types; <b><font color='#199C2C'>Skills and Ideals</font></b>. Skill Values are tied directly to a Skill, while Ideal Values represent broader concepts like passion or deceit. A Dynasty must have <b><font color='#199C2C'>at least one</font></b> and a <b><font color='#199C2C'>maximum of three</font></b> of each type. Some Values are <b><font color='#199C2C'>conflicting</font></b> and can't be selected together.\n\nCertain Dynasty Values unlock unique ways for Members to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Challenge</font></b> the current Head and claim the title for themselves.\n• <b><font color='#199C2C'>Swordsmanship Skill:</font></b> Unlocks Challenge via Duel\n• <b><font color='#199C2C'>Logic Skill:</font></b> Unlocks Challenge via Chess\n• <b><font color='#199C2C'>Vicious Ideal:</font></b> Unlocks Challenge via Fight"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Values2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:2437764d6043eb4a</T>
      <T n="text">0x9D6819D3<!--String: "Dynasty Members will have different <b><font color='#199C2C'>attitudes</font></b> towards the Dynasty’s Values, based on their<b><font color='#199C2C'> Personality Traits and Activity Preferences</font></b>. For example, a Member with the Likes Painting Preference or who is Creative will like the Painting Skill, and an Evil Member will despise the Caring Ideal but would support the Vicious Ideal.\n\nValues impact Member <b><font color='#199C2C'>behavior</font></b>. If a Member supports a chosen Value, they will be more likely to do the Encouraged Activities associated with it, but if they dislike the Value, they may do Discouraged Activities instead!\n\nIf the Head decides to <b><font color='#199C2C'>remove</font></b> an existing Value or <b><font color='#199C2C'>add</font></b> a new one, Members may react positively or negatively depending on their attitude towards the Value. Be careful; if the Head makes too many unpopular Value changes, it may lead to a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Unity Crisis</font></b>!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
